WEBVTT

00:01.020 --> 00:04.420
Oh, wow. My goodness.

00:04.421 --> 00:05.659
- Hon?
- Hmm?

00:05.660 --> 00:07.799
You notice a difference in my physique?

00:07.800 --> 00:09.179
I think because I've been outside

00:09.180 --> 00:10.519
pushing things and pulling,

00:10.520 --> 00:12.579
it seems to be having a real effect.

00:12.580 --> 00:13.990
- Really?
- I mean, I wouldn't go so far as

00:14.000 --> 00:17.010
to use the word "jacked," but
maybe "jacked adjacent"?

00:17.017 --> 00:18.159
Yeah, sure. I think...

00:18.160 --> 00:19.970
Yeah, I would call you
"jacked adjacent."

00:19.979 --> 00:22.059
Oh. Thanks for noticing that.

00:23.370 --> 00:24.739
Um, sweetie,

00:24.740 --> 00:25.960
is it okay if we put on

00:25.970 --> 00:27.359
my "Sounds of the Upper West Side"?

00:27.360 --> 00:29.200
'Cause my mom just sent
me a new recording.

00:29.210 --> 00:31.489
Well, it does make it
a little harder for me

00:31.490 --> 00:33.540
- to fall asleep.
- I know, but it's just so relaxing for me.

00:33.550 --> 00:36.459
I said cream cheese on the side, buddy!

00:36.460 --> 00:38.279
And cover your mouth when you cough,

00:38.280 --> 00:40.289
I could be pregnant!

00:40.290 --> 00:42.559
I just feel my stress melting away.

00:43.919 --> 00:45.189
Oh, so soothing.

00:45.190 --> 00:46.859
Maybe we could alternate between this

00:46.860 --> 00:48.590
and the sounds of war.

00:50.870 --> 00:52.439
Oh, my gosh!

00:52.440 --> 00:54.540
Honey, what's happening? What was that?

00:54.550 --> 00:55.759
Sounds like the chickens!
It's our babies!

00:55.760 --> 00:57.140
- You got to go do something!
- Yeah, I'm on it.

00:57.141 --> 00:58.809
- Oh, my God, our babies!
- All right, um, ooh, uh...

00:58.810 --> 01:00.219
I shouldn't go unarmed, right?

01:00.220 --> 01:01.349
You're buff as hell. You got this.

01:01.350 --> 01:02.389
No, no, I need like a bat or

01:02.390 --> 01:03.399
- some nunchucks or something.
- Honey!

01:03.400 --> 01:04.690
Take my weighted blanket.

01:04.700 --> 01:06.319
- A blanket?
- Is that okay? Is it too heavy?

01:06.320 --> 01:08.039
- Hon, we just went over how cut I am.
- I-I... I'm nervous!

01:08.040 --> 01:09.520
Okay.

01:09.528 --> 01:11.719
Is someone in here?!

01:11.720 --> 01:13.100
I have a weapon!

01:16.890 --> 01:18.059
Ahhh!

01:18.060 --> 01:19.454
Oh, Rudy!

01:19.455 --> 01:20.580
Is that your cape?

01:20.581 --> 01:22.199
No. It's not a cape.

01:22.200 --> 01:24.834
It's a... weighted blanket, for anxiety.

01:24.835 --> 01:26.753
I didn't know you wore
a cape for anxiety.

01:26.754 --> 01:28.671
Rudy, w-what are you doing in here?

01:28.672 --> 01:30.339
- What's with the feathers?
- Oh.

01:30.340 --> 01:31.499
Predator got in the coop.

01:31.500 --> 01:32.509
Oh, no.

01:32.510 --> 01:34.209
- I don't want to be too graphic...
- Thank you.

01:34.210 --> 01:35.804
... but you got a chicken with
her head ripped clean off.

01:35.805 --> 01:37.679
Guts everywhere, gizzard shredded,

01:37.680 --> 01:39.269
body turned completely inside out.

01:39.270 --> 01:41.350
Her eyes were open. She
saw the whole thing.

01:41.352 --> 01:42.644
Hard to believe so much blood

01:42.645 --> 01:43.978
comes from such a small creature.

01:43.979 --> 01:45.349
You can try to mop it
up, but you'll probably

01:45.350 --> 01:46.898
- just spread it around.
- Thank you, Rudy.

