01:50.903 --> 01:52.129
Hey, Deb!

01:52.130 --> 01:53.899
- Mail call!
- Yeah.

01:53.900 --> 01:55.890
Yeah, looks like just
a bunch of bills...

01:55.900 --> 01:57.780
- ... and there's a birth announcement.
- Oh. Oh!

01:57.785 --> 01:59.989
Thank you so much for always
going through our mail.

01:59.990 --> 02:01.340
Would it be more fun to just open it?

02:01.350 --> 02:02.497
Oh, I would love that.

02:02.498 --> 02:04.109
- I was kidding.
- Oh, okay. You know what?

02:04.110 --> 02:06.739
I get... I keep getting mail
addressed to Levine-Young...

02:06.740 --> 02:08.127
- Oh.
- ... instead of just Young.

02:08.127 --> 02:10.019
And if that's an error,
I can yell at somebody

02:10.020 --> 02:11.400
down at the main branch
to get that fixed.

02:11.410 --> 02:12.500
Oh, no, thank you so much.

02:12.508 --> 02:13.633
It's not an error.

02:13.634 --> 02:14.926
My last name is Levine,

02:14.927 --> 02:16.549
and Mike's last name is Young,

02:16.550 --> 02:18.346
and so when we got
married, we hyphenated it.

02:18.347 --> 02:20.890
Oh, 'cause Mike said
your name was Young.

02:20.891 --> 02:22.642
Huh. He did?

02:22.643 --> 02:25.029
- Mm-hmm.
- No. I took on his last name...

02:25.030 --> 02:26.999
- Mm-hmm.
- ... and he took on my last name. Um...

02:27.000 --> 02:29.399
Oh, wait, you said that
Mike took your last name?

02:29.400 --> 02:31.317
- Yeah. Yeah.
- Oh.

02:31.318 --> 02:32.819
He took...

02:32.820 --> 02:34.999
- Oh.
- He t...

02:35.000 --> 02:36.819
Oh, my God, I'm sorry.

02:36.820 --> 02:37.889
I'm so sorry.

02:37.890 --> 02:40.279
- Oh.
- I'm sorry, I just needed a laugh today.

02:40.280 --> 02:42.639
Kent's home. He's sick.
He's got the flu,

02:42.640 --> 02:45.019
- and there's diarrhea everywhere.
- Oh.

02:45.020 --> 02:47.333
And he misses the toilet,
and I'm just like, "Ugh."

02:47.334 --> 02:49.819
Anyway, tell Mike that
I said that he's doing

02:49.820 --> 02:52.088
a great job with this farm.
It's really coming along.

02:52.089 --> 02:53.489
Well, you can tell me that, too,

02:53.490 --> 02:56.467
'cause it's also my farm
and I work on it equally.

02:56.468 --> 02:58.511
Yeah, bye, Mrs. Young!

03:02.307 --> 03:03.808
Hey, guys!

03:03.809 --> 03:06.436
The egg mobile's really looking secure.

03:06.437 --> 03:08.521
Ready to roll up my
sleeves. How can I help?

03:08.522 --> 03:09.856
Why don't you make us
some good lemonade.

03:09.857 --> 03:12.358
Oh, you don't want her to do that.

03:12.359 --> 03:14.509
- Thank you, Mike.
- Yeah, when she makes it,

03:14.510 --> 03:16.349
it's, uh, got, like, a texture.

03:16.350 --> 03:18.906
You know, it's like a soup.
Like a thick bisque.

03:18.907 --> 03:20.779
- It's like a lemonade.
- Y'all had an intruder?

03:20.780 --> 03:22.300
- What? Oh, hey!
- Hey.

03:22.310 --> 03:24.349
Yes, I called 911, but
that was last night.

03:24.350 --> 03:25.979
- You're just coming now?
- Believe it or not,

03:25.980 --> 03:28.340
there isn't a code for a dead chicken.

03:28.350 --> 03:30.759
You can't call the sheriff
when a chicken dies,

03:30.760 --> 03:32.559
just like you can't
call the gynecologist

03:32.560 --> 03:33.899
when the Internet goes dead.

03:33.900 --> 03:34.909
Hmm.

03:34.910 --> 03:36.540
Constance?

03:37.500 --> 03:39.135
Rudy?

03:39.136 --> 03:41.199
Gonna be warm tonight.

03:41.200 --> 03:42.513
I suppose it is.

03:42.514 --> 03:44.682
So warm I might sweat
through the sheets.

03:44.683 --> 03:48.144
Well, I hope you have a... spare set.

03:48.145 --> 03:49.938
I do not.

03:50.820 --> 03:53.690
Well, the fireflies are
gonna be out tonight.

03:53.692 --> 03:57.696
I'm gonna be watching
if you want to come by.

04:01.658 --> 04:02.929
No.

04:02.930 --> 04:05.161
Copy that loud and clear.

04:05.162 --> 04:07.199
- Uh, exc... A-Are you sure?
- N-N-No, hold on, hold on.

04:07.200 --> 04:09.769
That would be a really nice
thing, to go see the fireflies,

04:09.770 --> 04:10.969
- 'cause they're so beautiful.
- Mm-hmm.

04:10.970 --> 04:12.099
They're the confetti of the angels.

04:12.100 --> 04:13.921
But I stand by my original response.

04:15.940 --> 04:17.569
- Um...
- Okay, well,

04:17.570 --> 04:19.809
- look, whoever killed Deirdre...
- Yes.

04:19.810 --> 04:21.499
- ... is still on the loose, alright?
- Yep.

04:21.500 --> 04:23.340
And I'm gonna be honest, I want revenge.

04:23.350 --> 04:25.580
- Yeah.
- I want vengeance!

04:25.620 --> 04:29.019
What's up with all
this hyper-macho thing

04:29.020 --> 04:30.779
that you've been doing
since we've been here?

04:30.780 --> 04:33.320
Mm. I don't know what
you're talking about.

04:37.330 --> 04:38.829
Please let me have this.

04:38.830 --> 04:41.363
I just feel like we're
falling into these patterns,

04:41.364 --> 04:42.460
and I don't like it.

04:42.470 --> 04:44.129
In New York, we had
an equal partnership.

04:44.130 --> 04:46.049
We were both independent,
capable people,

04:46.050 --> 04:48.119
and now you just expect me
to break out the lemons

04:48.120 --> 04:50.769
and the corn starch and make
lemonade for you and Rudy?

04:50.770 --> 04:52.279
So that's what's going on.

04:52.280 --> 04:54.639
Y-You don't need corn
starch in lemonade.

04:54.640 --> 04:55.759
- Oh.
- That's, I think, why it's chewy.

04:55.760 --> 04:57.349
And then Deb, a federal employee,

04:57.350 --> 04:59.380
got the go-ahead to call you Mike Young.

04:59.390 --> 05:01.740
- Um, that was just a time-saver.
- Yeah, but it...

05:01.750 --> 05:04.346
And, look, I-I don't want
you to just make lemonade.

05:04.347 --> 05:05.579
Thank you.

05:05.580 --> 05:07.806
I would like it if you could
bake some brownies as well.

05:07.807 --> 05:09.560
- Sorry, what?
- To take over to the Bowmans'

05:09.570 --> 05:11.311
so we have access to their
security cam footage.

05:11.312 --> 05:13.579
We gotta figure out what kind
of predator we're hunting,

05:13.580 --> 05:16.107
and Rudy says they have
security trail cams everywhere.

05:16.108 --> 05:17.739
So you want me to...

05:17.740 --> 05:18.760
make brownies?

05:18.770 --> 05:20.444
I'm sorry that this is how it is.

05:20.445 --> 05:21.519
But you're supposed to

05:21.520 --> 05:22.530
bring the brownies over.

05:22.531 --> 05:24.739
- There's just different expectations here.
- Okay, okay,

05:24.740 --> 05:27.000
but their expectations aren't
necessarily our expectations.

05:27.010 --> 05:28.479
- We're aligned in that, right?
- Agreed.

05:28.480 --> 05:30.285
- Great.
- A-And not to get all

05:30.286 --> 05:32.100
"look at the actual facts
of the situation,"

05:32.110 --> 05:34.660
but last night, when you
heard a scary noise,

05:34.670 --> 05:36.060
you wanted me to go check it out.

05:36.070 --> 05:37.319
I don't want you to take
this the wrong way,

05:37.320 --> 05:38.338
- but...
- Okay.

05:38.339 --> 05:39.980
... maybe here...

05:39.990 --> 05:43.260
you feel like you want me to
protect you a little more.

05:46.221 --> 05:48.055
You... You t... You took
that the wrong way.

05:48.056 --> 05:49.558
Yeah, I took it the wrong way.

05:50.630 --> 05:52.018
I hope you were not wearing an apron

05:52.019 --> 05:54.269
when you baked these brownies.

05:54.270 --> 05:56.000
And please tell me you
were wearing oven mitts

05:56.010 --> 05:57.400
when you took them out of the oven.

05:57.420 --> 05:59.769
Because otherwise, you
would burn yourself.

05:59.770 --> 06:01.060
Yeah.

06:01.070 --> 06:02.659
Okay, well, now that we all agree

06:02.660 --> 06:04.319
I'm a man who made brownies,

06:04.320 --> 06:06.113
I'd love to look at
that trail cam footage.

06:06.114 --> 06:08.460
Oh, yeah. Jacob, go check the footage.

06:08.470 --> 06:09.659
What time did you say the assault was?

06:09.660 --> 06:10.699
Around 10:30.

06:10.700 --> 06:12.560
I will be right back.

06:12.860 --> 06:14.100
Well... Well, not right back,

06:14.110 --> 06:16.329
because I do have to look
at the... the footage first,

06:16.330 --> 06:17.559
and then I'll come back and tell you...

06:17.560 --> 06:19.045
- We got it, son.
- Okay.

06:19.046 --> 06:21.239
Mike, obviously I've
lost all respect for you

06:21.240 --> 06:23.579
knowing that you baked these, but...

06:23.580 --> 06:26.169
this is the most delicious
brownie I have ever tasted.

06:26.170 --> 06:27.929
What is going on in my mouth right now?

06:27.930 --> 06:29.609
- My secret's a little sea salt.
- Mmm.

06:29.610 --> 06:32.209
Gives you that sweet, salty
back and forth, a little...

06:32.210 --> 06:33.919
Mm, I'm gonna pass on
that recipe advice to Kay

06:33.920 --> 06:37.280
when she gets back to town. She's
visiting her sister, Stacy...

06:37.780 --> 06:40.979
... who's a very, very beautiful woman.

06:40.980 --> 06:42.650
Hmm.

06:43.403 --> 06:44.949
Jacob!

06:44.950 --> 06:46.698
Did you find out what
got into Mike's coop?

06:46.699 --> 06:48.100
Yup.

06:48.110 --> 06:49.700
It was me.

06:51.036 --> 06:53.537
I killed your chicken, Mike.

06:54.800 --> 06:57.029
Hey. Rudy.

06:57.030 --> 06:59.669
Rio? I wasn't expecting
you. You're not Mike.

06:59.670 --> 07:01.869
Damn right I'm not Mike.
Mike's over at the Bowmans'.

07:01.870 --> 07:04.215
I'm here to murder an
animal. Let's do this.

07:04.216 --> 07:05.219
Why do you have so many keys?

07:05.220 --> 07:06.400
Were you a janitor in New York?

07:06.410 --> 07:08.719
No, this is to defend myself.

07:08.720 --> 07:10.304
From doorknobs?

07:10.305 --> 07:11.472
Actually, I'm glad you came.

07:11.473 --> 07:12.579
I'd like to ask what you thought

07:12.580 --> 07:14.479
about what happened
today with Constance.

07:14.480 --> 07:16.040
She came on a little strong, didn't she?

07:16.050 --> 07:18.539
I'm sorry, but would you be
talking about relationship drama

07:18.540 --> 07:20.889
if you were out here getting
ready for killing with a man?

07:20.890 --> 07:22.900
Maybe. If he was smaller than me.

07:23.986 --> 07:25.653
Can we talk about Constance now?

07:25.654 --> 07:28.979
No. We can only talk about
hunting-related items.

07:28.980 --> 07:29.991
We should split up.

07:29.992 --> 07:31.499
We'll cover more ground.

07:31.500 --> 07:33.239
- It's gonna be dark soon.
- Say what?

07:33.240 --> 07:34.829
You go one way, and I go the other.

07:34.830 --> 07:37.160
So you'll go out on your own,

07:37.170 --> 07:38.829
and I'll go out on my own.

07:38.830 --> 07:40.699
- Yeah, I said that twice now.
- Okay, so we'll be separate.

07:40.700 --> 07:41.789
Alright, great.

07:41.790 --> 07:43.239
This is good. I like this...

07:43.240 --> 07:44.320
- a very, very good plan.
- You hear anything,

07:44.330 --> 07:46.340
call me on the walkie. My
code name is "Potato."

07:46.341 --> 07:47.883
My code name is "Warrior."

07:47.884 --> 07:49.051
No. You're "Potato Three."

07:49.052 --> 07:50.302
What happened to "Potato Two"?

07:50.303 --> 07:51.310
You don't want to know.

07:52.020 --> 07:54.120
Over.

07:55.142 --> 07:56.789
So that's when I decided

07:56.790 --> 07:58.394
that all the chickens had to die.

07:58.395 --> 07:59.893
- No.
- Two chickens had to die.

07:59.894 --> 08:02.139
- It was only one.
- But I killed it lots of times.

08:02.140 --> 08:04.169
No. No, no, no, no. Something's up.

08:04.170 --> 08:05.179
Let's go look at the tape.

08:05.180 --> 08:07.020
No, no, no, Dad! Please
don't look at the tape!

08:13.420 --> 08:17.149
Well... this is embarrassing.

08:17.150 --> 08:19.080
Jacob killed your chicken.

08:24.463 --> 08:25.962
Cold one?

08:25.963 --> 08:27.640
We're... not gonna talk about

08:27.650 --> 08:28.841
what was on the footage?

08:28.842 --> 08:30.789
What's there to say?

08:30.790 --> 08:32.200
Jacob's a teenaged chicken-killer.

08:32.220 --> 08:34.099
Look, we all saw what was on the tapes,

08:34.100 --> 08:35.890
and, Beau, there's nothing
to be ashamed of.

08:35.892 --> 08:37.000
Of course not.

08:37.010 --> 08:38.899
If I was ashamed of
something, I'd act like it.

08:38.900 --> 08:42.270
- Yeah.
- No, sir.

08:46.310 --> 08:48.079
Okay, so, on the off chance

08:48.080 --> 08:49.959
that Jacob didn't kill my chicken,

08:49.960 --> 08:51.799
I think I need to search
for the predator.

08:51.800 --> 08:53.299
So I'll leave you two to talk.

08:53.300 --> 08:55.783
I imagine you have a
whole lot to get into...

08:55.784 --> 08:58.060
emotions and vulnerability, openness...

08:58.070 --> 08:59.769
Hold it!

08:59.770 --> 09:01.791
Why don't we help. We got all the gear.

09:01.792 --> 09:03.250
You'd be a fool not to
take advantage of us.

09:03.251 --> 09:06.962
Oh, yeah, Mike, take advantage
of us all night long.

09:06.963 --> 09:09.340
How could I say no to that?

09:09.341 --> 09:11.300
See this mother right here?

09:11.301 --> 09:12.679
Oh, wow. Oh.

09:12.680 --> 09:14.553
Got my shirt caught in a feed grinder.

09:14.554 --> 09:15.889
Nearly tore through my bicep.

09:15.890 --> 09:17.079
So badass.

09:17.080 --> 09:18.729
Still made it to my wedding on time.

09:18.730 --> 09:20.184
Had to army crawl ten miles.

09:20.185 --> 09:21.977
I didn't even go to the hospital.

09:21.978 --> 09:24.829
Only help I had was from
Dr. Kentucky Bourbon.

09:24.830 --> 09:26.149
You know what I'm saying?

09:26.150 --> 09:27.880
- Mm.
- So tough.

09:28.700 --> 09:30.480
Wow! We taking all those?

09:30.487 --> 09:31.639
Scared of the manpower?

09:31.640 --> 09:32.738
No problemo.

09:32.739 --> 09:34.939
We'll go with a blade instead.

09:34.940 --> 09:37.200
Jacob, why don't you grab a ma-che-te.

09:38.411 --> 09:39.620
Ding!

09:39.621 --> 09:42.039
Oh, wow. Hey. Okay.

09:42.040 --> 09:43.958
Jacob, be careful, yeah?
It's probably sharp.

09:43.959 --> 09:45.251
Yeah. Yes.

09:45.252 --> 09:46.619
It is very sharp.

09:46.620 --> 09:49.964
But it's safe if you
know what you're doing.

09:51.210 --> 09:52.579
Ohh...

09:52.580 --> 09:53.589
Oh!

09:53.590 --> 09:54.969
I'm... fine.

09:54.970 --> 09:56.599
Your thumb is on the floor.

09:56.600 --> 09:58.080
That's not where it's supposed to be.

10:00.550 --> 10:02.226
- It's not on your hand right now.
- Use this.

10:02.227 --> 10:03.227
Ooh.

10:03.228 --> 10:05.169
We need to go to the hospital.

10:05.170 --> 10:07.309
- My son lost his thumb.
- Yeah.

10:07.310 --> 10:09.567
- Oh, my God!
- Okay, I'll drive. I'll drive.

10:09.568 --> 10:11.360
You go out and be with your dad.

10:11.361 --> 10:12.709
- Aah, gross!
- I just touched it.

10:12.710 --> 10:13.880
- Okay. Ugh.
- Ahh!

