Okay...

10:26.260 --> 10:28.129
Hey, Potato.

10:28.130 --> 10:29.369
How's it going over there?

10:29.370 --> 10:30.919
Did you see the critter, Potato Three?

10:30.920 --> 10:32.119
No, not exactly.

10:32.120 --> 10:34.039
- Uh, but...
- Then we should stay off the walkies

10:34.040 --> 10:35.880
unless there's an emergency. Over.

10:36.880 --> 10:39.309
It is an emergency in a way,

10:39.310 --> 10:42.141
'cause we should probably...
talk about Constance.

10:42.142 --> 10:44.518
Boy, is that a tough nut to crack.

10:44.519 --> 10:47.229
Why do you think you said no to
going to see those fireflies?

10:47.230 --> 10:49.379
Because she's not the one who's
supposed to ask me out on a date.

10:49.380 --> 10:51.479
That's the man's job.
What's left for me to do?

10:51.480 --> 10:52.519
Bat my eyelashes

10:52.520 --> 10:54.402
- and blow sweet kissies?
- Sure, sure, sure.

10:54.403 --> 10:56.499
You're used to the man doing the asking,

10:56.500 --> 10:58.489
but, you know, there's
lots of ways to do things.

10:58.490 --> 11:00.919
Like when you bring me
dirty laundry to do,

11:00.920 --> 11:02.679
sometimes Mike does it.
There's a very good chance

11:02.680 --> 11:04.819
that Mike washed the underwear
that you're wearing right now.

11:04.820 --> 11:06.220
A-And it's important to remember

11:06.230 --> 11:07.979
that the reason you like Constance

11:07.980 --> 11:09.040
is because she's strong

11:09.044 --> 11:11.963
and because she does
things for herself, right?

11:13.380 --> 11:14.840
Rudy?

11:16.050 --> 11:17.069
Rudy, you with me?

11:19.580 --> 11:22.010
- I need to go see Constance.
- Wait, right now?

11:22.015 --> 11:24.399
No, Rudy, listen to me, I think
that this Constance thing

11:24.400 --> 11:27.309
could be really the symptom of a
much larger problem, and I...

11:27.310 --> 11:28.799
That's okay. I'm very happy
with everything else

11:28.800 --> 11:29.839
that's wrong with me.

11:29.840 --> 11:30.857
Goodbye, Potato Three.

11:30.858 --> 11:32.479
Potato, over and out.

11:32.480 --> 11:34.829
No, it's not over till
we both "over." Over?

11:34.830 --> 11:36.129
Damn it!

11:40.450 --> 11:42.099
Not cool!

11:47.624 --> 11:48.749
Aah!

11:48.750 --> 11:50.160
Aah! Weasel!

11:50.170 --> 11:53.530
Oh, God, I should've just
made the stupid brownies!

11:55.060 --> 11:56.940
Alright, well, it's gonna
take about an hour

11:56.950 --> 11:58.999
to get to the hospital,
but if all goes well,

11:59.000 --> 12:01.929
old Jacob's gonna be hitchhiking
with strangers in no time..

12:01.930 --> 12:04.289
Do you need me to drive to the hospital?

12:04.290 --> 12:06.725
No, I-I got... I got it.

12:06.726 --> 12:09.311
Um... so, it's no big deal,

12:09.312 --> 12:12.399
just a little FYI, the weasel is, um...

12:12.400 --> 12:14.199
... is inside our house,

12:14.200 --> 12:17.349
and I just need you to come home
and kind of take care of it.

12:17.350 --> 12:18.570
I would love nothing more

12:18.571 --> 12:20.531
- than to take care of that weasel, but...
- Okay, great!

12:20.532 --> 12:22.190
So just, you know, come on home

12:22.200 --> 12:24.110
and... and take care of it now.

12:24.119 --> 12:25.661
- I can't.
- What do you mean, you can't?

12:25.662 --> 12:27.496
What do you want to hear? I'm scared.

12:27.497 --> 12:28.639
I'm a fragile, little woman

12:28.640 --> 12:30.110
with fragile, little birdy bones, okay?

12:30.120 --> 12:32.660
I'm mentally and physically
incapable of survival.

12:32.669 --> 12:34.790
Does that work? Is that enough?
Can you come home now?

12:34.796 --> 12:36.139
I can't come home right now.

12:36.140 --> 12:38.169
I'm trying like hell
to keep a thumb fresh!

12:38.170 --> 12:39.579
Hey, Dad, what do you think

12:39.580 --> 12:41.379
of the Huskers' new wide receiver, huh?

12:41.380 --> 12:42.399
He's the top recruit.

12:42.400 --> 12:43.637
- Yep.
- A good get.

12:43.638 --> 12:45.718
You remember, you thought
Michigan was gonna get him?

12:47.360 --> 12:49.259
They're talking about
football. They're fine!

12:49.260 --> 12:50.519
You got to come home!

12:50.520 --> 12:52.813
It's way more messed
up than that, sweetie.

12:52.814 --> 12:55.739
I will come protect you from
the weasel when I get back.

12:55.740 --> 12:57.079
Oh, but that could be all night, babe.

12:57.080 --> 12:58.109
- Ugh!
- Oh, no, no, no, no, no, no.

12:58.110 --> 12:59.279
- I-I just...
- Shut this, shut this, shut this.

12:59.280 --> 13:00.979
You have one job, Beau!

13:00.980 --> 13:02.379
To hold the thumb!

13:02.380 --> 13:04.242
What's happening, Mike? Honey?

13:04.243 --> 13:05.419
I love you, but I gotta go.

13:05.420 --> 13:06.429
Mike!

13:09.560 --> 13:10.780
Mm.

13:13.230 --> 13:14.543
Who died?

13:14.544 --> 13:16.739
Mom... there's a weasel in my house.

13:16.740 --> 13:18.420
Oh, my God! Did it touch you?

13:18.423 --> 13:19.590
Remember your cousin Neary?

13:19.591 --> 13:21.300
She got rabies from a weasel.

13:21.301 --> 13:23.802
Her brain is mush now. Complete mush.

13:23.803 --> 13:26.013
She still likes animals,
though, which is nice.

13:26.014 --> 13:27.306
How come I've never
heard of this person?

13:27.307 --> 13:28.439
What, am I just gonna bring up

13:28.440 --> 13:30.160
a mushy-brained relative on a whim?

13:30.170 --> 13:31.393
I don... Mom, listen.

13:31.394 --> 13:32.439
Mike's not here,

13:32.440 --> 13:34.890
and he's not gonna be here
for another few hours,

13:34.900 --> 13:36.560
and I don't know what to do.

13:36.566 --> 13:39.318
In New York, I remember being
so strong and independent.

13:39.319 --> 13:42.159
Now I don't know who I am anymore,

13:42.160 --> 13:46.159
and it's like I-I need
Mike so much out here,

13:46.160 --> 13:47.739
and it scares me.

13:47.740 --> 13:49.959
- Why?
- Because you've always taught me

13:49.960 --> 13:51.914
- to fend for myself.
- Yeah. So?

13:51.915 --> 13:53.479
So how can I be strong and independent

13:53.480 --> 13:55.040
if I need him so much?

13:55.043 --> 13:57.829
Being strong doesn't mean
doing everything on your own.

13:57.830 --> 13:59.079
That's why you have a partner...

13:59.080 --> 14:00.714
so they can be strong when you're not.

14:00.715 --> 14:02.059
Nobody's strong all the time,

14:02.060 --> 14:03.339
except Monica Lewinsky,

14:03.340 --> 14:05.761
and you know I've been at her
side from the very beginning.

14:05.762 --> 14:08.779
But, Rio, you're not losing yourself.

14:08.780 --> 14:11.433
You're just learning how
to rely on each other.

14:11.434 --> 14:12.849
Right.

14:15.090 --> 14:17.314
Hey, Mom.

14:17.315 --> 14:19.939
Were you the one who taught me
to put keys between my fingers

14:19.940 --> 14:21.150
to make them a weapon?

14:21.152 --> 14:22.259
No.

14:22.260 --> 14:24.099
You learned that one on your own.

14:24.100 --> 14:26.819
Remember when you key-holed
that flasher on the subway?

14:26.820 --> 14:30.119
Oh, my God, that was one of the
proudest moments of my life.

14:30.120 --> 14:32.371
What?! Was that the weasel?!

14:32.372 --> 14:33.609
- I got this.
- Rio?

14:33.610 --> 14:34.740
Where'd you go?

14:34.750 --> 14:36.870
- Don't put me down!
- I'm coming for your weasel ass.

14:41.990 --> 14:44.133
Hi, Constance.

14:44.134 --> 14:45.759
Rudy. Why are you here?

14:45.760 --> 14:47.386
A man washed my underwear.

14:47.387 --> 14:50.499
Everyone in this town needs to
learn what an emergency is.

14:50.500 --> 14:51.509
No, wait.

14:51.510 --> 14:53.929
I...

14:53.930 --> 14:56.859
It's really hard for me to change.

14:56.860 --> 14:58.429
But I'd like it if you'd...

14:58.430 --> 15:00.275
ask me out again sometime.

15:02.569 --> 15:05.439
Have a nice evening, Constance.

15:23.756 --> 15:25.216
The doctors know what they're doing.

15:25.217 --> 15:26.859
- Yeah.
- I saw a lot of coolers

15:26.860 --> 15:29.178
when we checked in. I think
this is the place people come.

15:29.179 --> 15:30.839
Let's hope so, huh?

15:30.840 --> 15:32.740
Hey, uh...

15:33.900 --> 15:35.934
... it was me crying on that video.

15:35.935 --> 15:37.429
Oh. Really?

15:37.430 --> 15:39.420
Yeah.

15:44.210 --> 15:46.549
I cry sometimes.

15:46.550 --> 15:48.809
Sure.

15:48.810 --> 15:52.860
I do it alone so nobody
has to see it, but I cry.

15:54.750 --> 15:58.916
Sometimes I... I cry so hard,
I can feel it in my nuts.

15:58.917 --> 16:00.834
Mm.

16:00.835 --> 16:01.919
Do you wanna know why?

16:01.920 --> 16:03.378
You bet I do, Beau.

16:03.379 --> 16:05.005
Farming's not what it used to be.

16:05.006 --> 16:06.539
You think I want to sell bull semen

16:06.540 --> 16:08.969
to the Mudanjiang prefecture in China?

16:08.970 --> 16:10.177
No.

16:10.178 --> 16:12.012
But I had to diversify.

16:12.013 --> 16:13.759
I want to keep that
bull semen for myself

16:13.760 --> 16:15.510
like my dad did, and his dad.

16:15.517 --> 16:18.310
- Sure.
- It kills me that Jacob saw me like that.

16:18.311 --> 16:19.437
Oh, come... Beau.

16:20.600 --> 16:22.099
- Hey.
- Don't look at me right now.

16:22.100 --> 16:23.160
Well, where do you want me to look?

16:23.170 --> 16:25.460
- Just don't look right at me.
- Okay.

16:29.190 --> 16:31.659
Sorry, it's gotta be you.

16:31.660 --> 16:35.059
Listen, I saw my dad cry once.

16:35.060 --> 16:38.179
You know, we were on a long
drive, just the two of us,

16:38.180 --> 16:40.519
when, uh, Bob Seger came on the radio.

16:40.520 --> 16:42.439
Gotta love Bob Seger.

16:42.440 --> 16:44.299
Mm-hmm. Yeah.

16:44.300 --> 16:46.979
I mean, my dad's not an emotional guy,

16:46.980 --> 16:49.039
but when "Against The Wind" came on...

16:49.040 --> 16:50.409
Oh!

16:50.410 --> 16:52.949
... boy, that was the whole ballgame.

16:52.950 --> 16:56.619
He told me how it reminded
him of my mom and...

16:56.620 --> 16:59.439
apparently, they had made love
to that song the night before,

16:59.440 --> 17:01.079
which really bummed me out to hear,

17:01.080 --> 17:02.689
but the point remains,

17:02.690 --> 17:04.789
you know, by him opening up like that,

17:04.790 --> 17:06.605
it gave me permission to feel.

17:06.606 --> 17:09.819
You shouldn't be embarrassed
you cried in front of Jacob.

17:09.829 --> 17:10.946
You should be proud of that.

17:10.948 --> 17:12.138
- Mr. Bowman?
- Yeah.

17:12.140 --> 17:14.118
Jacob's doing great.
He's resting right now,

17:14.119 --> 17:15.519
but you can see him in a little bit.

17:15.520 --> 17:16.679
Okay, thank you.

17:16.680 --> 17:18.519
- Thank you.
- He's fine.

17:18.520 --> 17:19.598
That's what we want to hear.

17:19.599 --> 17:20.638
Aah!

17:20.640 --> 17:22.179
He... He... He's fine.

17:22.180 --> 17:24.079
Yeah.

17:25.810 --> 17:27.878
Ugh!

17:31.380 --> 17:32.859
Want me to get us another bag of those?

17:32.860 --> 17:34.160
Don't you... Don't you leave me.

17:34.170 --> 17:35.719
Okay.

17:35.720 --> 17:37.889
- Great.
- Don't you leave me.

17:37.890 --> 17:39.290
Please.

17:39.300 --> 17:41.300
Ugh!

17:50.200 --> 17:54.269
Weasel, I know you don't
understand words,

17:54.270 --> 17:56.349
but I hope that my tone

17:56.350 --> 17:59.479
is soothing and stern enough
for you to understand

17:59.480 --> 18:03.059
that I would really like you to leave.

18:10.548 --> 18:12.090
Ahhhhh! Get off!

18:12.091 --> 18:13.133
Get rid of it!

18:13.134 --> 18:15.029
- Hey, Thumbelina.
- Hey.

18:15.030 --> 18:17.229
- How you doing?
- I'm good.

18:17.230 --> 18:19.431
I told them I didn't
need any anesthesia.

18:19.432 --> 18:21.767
And then I do not
remember what happened.

18:21.768 --> 18:23.639
Listen.

18:23.640 --> 18:25.520
This scar?

18:25.521 --> 18:27.899
That S.O.B. hurt so bad I passed out.

18:27.900 --> 18:30.379
Then I woke up covered in urine.

18:30.380 --> 18:33.379
I had peed myself like a newborn.

18:33.380 --> 18:35.560
And then I spit up all over
your mama's wedding dress.

18:35.570 --> 18:38.040
- W-What?
- And Dr. Kentucky Bourbon?

18:38.050 --> 18:40.599
Well, actually a lady doctor

18:40.600 --> 18:41.989
named Millicent G. Tubbs.

18:41.990 --> 18:44.039
The point is, I'm only human.

18:44.040 --> 18:45.620
And that's what you saw on that tape.

18:45.625 --> 18:47.250
And I'm...

18:48.660 --> 18:50.921
I'm so happy that you're okay.

18:50.922 --> 18:52.749
Me too, Dad.

18:53.780 --> 18:56.660
It hurt so much when I cut my
thumb off with that knife!

18:57.650 --> 18:59.669
Oh.

18:59.670 --> 19:00.680
Get outta my way!

19:00.690 --> 19:01.789
My son's in there!

19:01.790 --> 19:02.805
- Mom.
- Jacob!

19:02.806 --> 19:04.300
Oh, my God. My sweet baby.

19:04.310 --> 19:06.728
- Kay.
- Oh, I'm good.

19:06.729 --> 19:08.639
I'm so glad the angels didn't take you.

19:08.640 --> 19:11.340
The angels saved his thumb,
but they took your cooler.

19:14.028 --> 19:15.987
I don't know why I said that.

19:15.988 --> 19:17.470
I would've been here sooner,

19:17.480 --> 19:19.389
but your Aunt Stacy and
I were stuck in a tree

19:19.390 --> 19:20.534
hunting a ten-point buck.

19:20.535 --> 19:22.243
I wanted to nab a six-pointer,

19:22.244 --> 19:24.359
but you know your Aunt
Stacy's a real size queen.

19:24.360 --> 19:25.839
- Right.
- I love you so much.

19:25.840 --> 19:27.080
I love you, Mama.

19:27.083 --> 19:28.799
I don't know what happened here,

19:28.800 --> 19:30.790
but I choose to blame you.

19:38.000 --> 19:39.179
Rio?!

19:39.180 --> 19:40.960
Hon?!

19:41.020 --> 19:42.719
Hello, Mike.

19:42.720 --> 19:44.040
Oh.

19:44.050 --> 19:46.579
Hey. I'm so sorry, but I'm here now,

19:46.580 --> 19:48.604
- and I want to kill the weasel.
- You're too late.

19:48.605 --> 19:49.999
Oh!

19:50.000 --> 19:52.232
Wait, you did this? By yourself?

19:52.233 --> 19:53.400
How?

19:53.401 --> 19:55.110
- You key-holed that mother.
- No, no, no.

19:55.111 --> 19:56.879
He was just sort of
attracted to shiny stuff,

19:56.880 --> 19:57.905
and that sort of did the trick.

19:57.906 --> 19:59.499
- Aah!
- Watch. See, he loves this.

20:01.240 --> 20:03.479
Wow. Thank God. I was nervous one of us

20:03.480 --> 20:05.077
was gonna end up like your cousin Neary.

20:05.078 --> 20:06.999
- How do you know about that?
- Hon, she was at our wedding.

20:07.000 --> 20:08.009
- She was? I don't...
- Remember? Yeah.

20:08.010 --> 20:09.850
Who do you think that
uniformed nurse was with?

20:10.280 --> 20:11.500
- Right?
- Oh.

20:11.502 --> 20:13.044
- Forgot about that.
- Honey, listen.

20:13.045 --> 20:15.005
I want to bake you brownies.

20:15.006 --> 20:16.590
- Yeah?
- Yes.

20:16.591 --> 20:19.379
And I do not want to make you lemonade.

20:19.380 --> 20:20.439
- I want that, too.
- Yeah.

20:20.440 --> 20:23.489
When we got married, I took
your name because we're a team.

20:23.490 --> 20:25.459
And I'm still Mike Levine-Young.

20:25.460 --> 20:27.476
- I cook, I clean...
- Mm-hmm.

20:27.477 --> 20:29.394
... and I make it happen
between the sheets.

20:29.395 --> 20:31.559
- Yes, you do.
- That's who I am.

20:31.560 --> 20:32.897
Oh, my goodness!

20:32.898 --> 20:34.470
- Oh, it's okay.
- Boy, he is angry, huh?

20:34.480 --> 20:36.400
No, this is him at a three.

20:36.402 --> 20:37.443
Should we keep him?

20:37.444 --> 20:39.560
- No, absolutely not.
- No, we won't.

20:39.570 --> 20:40.890
- It's a bad idea.
- Yeah, I know.

20:42.460 --> 20:45.380
Ugh!

20:45.880 --> 20:47.179
- Mm.
- Mm.

20:47.180 --> 20:48.455
Hmm-hmm.

20:48.456 --> 20:49.689
No weighted blanket?

20:49.690 --> 20:50.707
Mnh-mnh.

20:50.708 --> 20:52.790
It's covered in weasel feces.

20:52.800 --> 20:54.449
Mm.

20:54.450 --> 20:57.259
Want me to put on your "Sounds
of the Upper West Side"?

20:57.260 --> 20:58.689
No.

20:58.690 --> 21:01.129
I like the sounds of Nebraska.

21:01.130 --> 21:03.160
Mm.

21:04.550 --> 21:05.597
W-Who's there?

21:05.598 --> 21:07.179
Rudy!

21:07.180 --> 21:08.899
What are you doing here?

21:08.900 --> 21:10.579
I figured it's about time
I did my own laundry.

21:10.580 --> 21:11.699
Yeah, but in our sink?

21:11.700 --> 21:13.354
The washer and dryer
are in the basement.

21:13.355 --> 21:15.439
I don't like being underground.

21:15.440 --> 21:17.442
- Please tell me that's food.
- I hope not.

21:17.443 --> 21:19.486
My underwear's in there.

21:19.487 --> 21:20.879
Hot and fresh.

21:20.880 --> 21:22.159
- Oh, wow.
- Wow.

21:22.160 --> 21:23.449
Yeah. Right where we eat breakfast.

21:23.450 --> 21:24.492
- Yep, there it is.
- Okay.

